<dl id="n22041j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n22" href="#n22041j">N22 (VI.B.17)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n22all.htm#n22041j"> 41(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> &lsquo;good&rsquo; friars</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> story 32: The poor simple women, who believed the good friars were more like angels than terrestrial beings, did not refuse to pay the tithe. There was not one who did not pay in her turn, from the highest to the lowest, even the wife of the Lord was not excused. <small> Robert B. Douglas, trans., <a name="RBDM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RBDM"><cite title="source">ONE HUNDRED MERRIE AND DELIGHTSOME STORIES</cite></a> (1923) Story 32</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
